<!-- ===== TEACHING PHILOSOPHY ===== -->
<section class="philosophy-section" id="philosophy">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label">Teaching Philosophy</div>
    <h2 class="section-heading">Three Principles That<br>Drive Every Classroom</h2>
    <div class="pillars-grid">

      <div class="pillar-card">
        <span class="pillar-number">I</span>
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M21 16V8a2 2 0 0 0-1-1.73l-7-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 0l-7 4A2 2 0 0 0 3 8v8a2 2 0 0 0 1 1.73l7 4a2 2 0 0 0 2 0l7-4A2 2 0 0 0 21 16z"/><polyline points="3.27 6.96 12 12.01 20.73 6.96"/><line x1="12" y1="22.08" x2="12" y2="12"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Industry Grounds Every Concept</h3>
        <p>Every derivation, every sensor specification, every measurement standard taught in the classroom is paired with a real production, field, or product context drawn from 25 years of engineering practice. Students leave knowing not just the how, but the why it matters when the stakes are real.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar-card">
        <span class="pillar-number">II</span>
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Uncertainty Is Not an Afterthought</h3>
        <p>Measurement without uncertainty quantification is guesswork. Students in both courses are trained to propagate error, interpret calibration records, and communicate confidence intervals the way a practicing engineer would in an ISO-compliant or regulated environment.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pillar-card">
        <span class="pillar-number">III</span>
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3>The Midlife-PhD Perspective</h3>
        <p>Dr. Tipton entered the PhD program after serving as a CEO. That path is unusual, and it shapes how every course is structured: with deep respect for what students are capable of, genuine enthusiasm for the discipline, and zero tolerance for teaching material that has no life outside a lecture hall.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

