      <div class="course-body">
        <div class="course-description">
          <p>Measurements and Instrumentation provides a rigorous foundation in the principles and practice of engineering measurement. The course covers the complete measurement chain from physical transduction through signal conditioning, data acquisition, and statistical analysis, with <strong>strong emphasis on calibration methodology, uncertainty quantification, and real instrument systems</strong>.</p>
          <p>Topics are introduced through first principles and immediately anchored in application contexts drawn from Dr. Tipton's industry experience in manufacturing, product development, and process control. Students leave with hands-on competency in strain and temperature sensing, the ability to read and interpret calibration records, and a working understanding of data acquisition system architecture.</p>
        </div>

