          <p>Mechatronics 1 introduces students to the integrated design of mechanical, electrical, and computational systems. The course builds from electrical fundamentals through analog circuits, microcontroller programming, and actuator control, always with the goal of producing <strong>students who can design, build, and debug complete electromechanical systems</strong>.</p>
          <p>Lab sessions are central to the course. Students work on physical systems throughout the semester, encountering the noise, variability, and unexpected behavior that simulation cannot replicate. The course draws explicitly on Dr. Tipton's background in manufacturing and product development to frame each concept in the context of real system design constraints.</p>
